activeBundles(uint96).details: Returns the number of active bundles for the given pool.

activeRisks(uint96).details: Returns the number of active risks for the specified product.

authorizedFunctions(address).details: Returns the number of authorized functions for the given target.

bundles(uint96).details: Returns the total number of registered bundles for the given pool.

claims(uint96).details: Returns the number of claims for the given policy NFT ID.

getActiveBundleNftId(uint96,uint256).details: Returns the active bunde NFT ID for the given pool and index.

getActiveRiskId(uint96,uint256).details: Returns the active risk ID for the given product NFT ID and (active) risk index.

getAuthorizedFunction(address,uint256).details: Returns the authorized function info for the given target and index.

getBalanceAmount(uint96).details: Returns the current token balance amount for the given component NFT ID. The balance amount includes the fee amount.

getBundleInfo(uint96).details: Returns the bundle info for the given bundle NFT ID.

getBundleNftId(uint96,uint256).details: Returns the bunde NFT ID for the given pool and index.

getBundleState(uint96).details: Returns the bundle state for the given bundle NFT ID.

getClaimId(uint256).details: Returns the claim ID for the given policy NFT ID and index.

getClaimInfo(uint96,uint16).details: Returns the claim info for the given policy NFT ID and claim ID.

getClaimState(uint96,uint16).details: Returns the current claim state for the given policy NFT ID and claim ID.

getComponentInfo(uint96).details: Returns the component info for the given component NFT ID.

getFeeAmount(uint96).details: Returns the current fee amount for the given NFT ID. The target NFT ID may reference a component, a distributor or a bundle.

getFeeInfo(uint96).details: Returns the current fee settings for the given product NFT ID.

getInstanceOwnerRole().details: Returns the role ID for the instance owner role. This role may be used as a "root" admin role for other custom roles defined for this instance.

getLockedAmount(uint96).details: Returns the currently locked amount for the given NFT ID. Locked amounts are only tracked for bundles, not for pool. To get the  pool locked amount, then locked amounts of the bundles contained in the  pool must be summed up. The target NFT ID may only a bundle.

getPayoutId(uint16,uint24).details: Returns the payout ID for the given claim ID and index.

getPayoutInfo(uint96,uint40).details: Returns the payout info for the given policy NFT ID and payout ID.

getPayoutState(uint96,uint40).details: Returns the payout state for the given policy NFT ID and payout ID.

getPolicyForBundle(uint96,uint256).details: Returns the linked policy NFT ID for the given risk ID and index.

getPolicyForRisk(bytes8,uint256).details: Returns the linked policy NFT ID for the given risk ID and index.

getPolicyInfo(uint96).details: Returns the info for the given policy NFT ID.

getPolicyState(uint96).details: Returns the state for the given policy NFT ID.

getPoolInfo(uint96).details: Returns the pool info for the given pool NFT ID.

getPremiumInfo(uint96).details: Returns the premium info for the given policy NFT ID.

getPremiumState(uint96).details: Returns the premium state for the given policy NFT ID.

getProduct(uint256).details: Returns th product NFT ID for the given index.

getProductInfo(uint96).details: Returns the product info for the given product NFT ID.

getRegistry().details: Returns the registry this instance is registered in.

getRemainingClaimableAmount(uint96).details: Returns the remaining claimable amount for the given policy NFT ID. The remaining claimable amount is the difference between the sum insured amount and total approved claim amounts so far.

getRequestInfo(uint64).details: Returns the request info for the given oracle request ID.

getRequestState(uint64).details: Returns the request info for the given oracle request ID.

getRiskId(uint96,uint256).details: Returns the risk ID for the given product NFT ID and (registered) risk index.

getRiskInfo(bytes8).details: Returns the risk info for the given risk ID.

getRiskState(bytes8).details: Returns the risk state for the given risk ID.

getRoleForName(string).details: Returns the role ID for the given index.

getRoleId(uint256).details: Returns the role ID for the given index.

getRoleInfo(uint64).details: Returns the role info for the given role ID.

getRoleMember(uint64,uint256).details: Returns the member (account address) for the given role ID and index.

getTargetAddress(uint256).details: Returns the target address for the given index.

getTargetInfo(address).details: Returns the target info for the given target address.

getToken(uint96).details: Returns the registered token for the given component NFT ID.

getTokenHandler(uint96).details: Returns the token handler for the given component NFT ID. The token handler manages all transfers from/to the component's wallet. To allow a component to collect funds from an account, it has to create a corresponding allowance from the account to the address of the component's token handler.

getWallet(uint96).details: Returns the current wallet address for the given component NFT ID. The wallet address is either the component's own address or any other wallet address specified by the component owner. The wallet holds the component's funds. Tokens collected by the component are transferred to the wallet and  Tokens distributed from the component are transferred from this wallet.

initialize().details: This initializer needs to be called from the instance itself.

initializeWithInstance(address).details: Initializer to upgrade instance reader via instance service

isLocked(address).details: Returns true iff the given target is locked.

isProductRisk(uint96,bytes8).details: Returns true if the specified risk exists for the given product NFT ID.

isRoleActive(uint64).details: Returns true iff the provided role ID is active.

isRoleAdmin(uint64,address).details: Returns true iff the given account is an admin of the specified role ID. Role admins may grant and revoke the role to other accounts.

isRoleCustom(uint64).details: Returns true iff the provided role ID represents a custom role ID.

isRoleMember(uint64,address).details: Returns true iff the given account is a member of the specified role ID.

payouts(uint96,uint16).details: Returns the number of payouts for the given policy NFT ID and claim ID.

policiesForBundle(uint96).details: Returns the number of linked policies for the given bundle NFT ID.

policiesForRisk(bytes8).details: Returns the number of linked policies for the given risk ID.

policyIsActive(uint96).details: Returns true iff policy is active.

products().details: Returns the number of registered products.

risks(uint96).details: Returns the total number of registered risks for the specified product.

roleExists(uint64).details: Returns true iff the provided role ID is defined for this instance.

roleMembers(uint64).details: Returns the number of members (accounts) for the given role ID.

roles().details: Returns the number of defined roles.

targetExists(address).details: Returns true iff the given target is defined for this instance.

targets().details: Returns the number of targets (contracts) defined for this instance.

toFunction(bytes4,string).details: Returns a function info for the given function selector and function name. The function selector must not be zero and the function name must not be empty.
